        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Judiciary. Quieting the war party</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>San Felipe</placeName> <date when="1835-07-31">July 31st 1835</date></p>

<p><persName>Majr Ira R. Lewis</persName>,</p>

<p>Dear <persName>Majr</persName></p>

<p>I am again in this <placeName>elisium </placeName>and very anxious to see you for many reasons.
I am here for the purpose of organizing the <persName>Court</persName>, and of representing the
<placeName>Municipality of Gonzales</placeName> in the approaching council convoked by the <persName>Chief</persName>.
Old <persName>Capt. Martin</persName> and myself have come apparently to a good 
understanding, and he will support the <persName>court</persName>.</p>

<p>I shall proceed in a short time to <placeName>Nacogdoches </placeName>for the same purpose
and to quiet the <persName>war party</persName>. They tell me you have given the war whoop;
is it so Come, now be quiet.</p>

<p>I wish to swear in the <persName>officers </persName>before I leave here. Please send up my
trunks, books, etc. by the first opportunity, as I shall need them. Please
present my kindest remembrances to <persName>Mrs. Lewis,</persName> and to my little sweet
hearts. Oh! how much older I have grown.</p>

<p><persName>T. Jefferson Chambers </persName>[Rubric]</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Majr Ira R. Lewis</persName> <placeName>Matagorda</placeName></p>


        </div1>
